data.title: Gina Tognoni Biography
data.meta_description: Read all about Gina Tognoni with TV Guide's exclusive biography including their list of awards, celeb facts and more at TV Guide.
data.text:
Fast Facts

Named Miss Rhode Island Teen All-American in 1993

Was originally set to attend Emerson College, but decided to focus on her acting career instead

Originated the role of Kelly Cramer on One Life to Live in 1995; stepped into the role of Dinah on Guiding Light in 2004; and in 2010, she reprised the role of Kelly Cramer on OLTL

GL brought her a Daytime Emmy (her first) for Outstanding Supporting Actress in 2006

She won again for the same role in 2008

In 2009, she joined the cast of the Web series Venice, produced by her former GL costar Crystal Chappell
